    "{\n",
    " \"cells\": [\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"markdown\",\"metadata\":{},\"source\":[\"# Question Type Classification\\n\",\"\\n\",\"**NLP Project 10 of 100**\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"markdown\",\"metadata\":{},\"source\":[\"## Project Overview\\n\",\"\\n\",\"Classify questions into types: **factual, opinion, procedural, causal, yes/no, and comparison**. This is useful for QA routing, chatbot design, and search intent understanding.\\n\",\"\\n\",\"## Learning Objectives\\n\",\"1. Build a multi-class question classifier.\\n\",\"2. Engineer features from question syntax (wh-words, punctuation, length).\\n\",\"3. Compare TF-IDF + ML vs lightweight transformer approaches.\\n\",\"4. Understand how question type affects downstream QA pipeline design.\\n\",\"\\n\",\"## Problem Statement\\n\",\"Given a question text, predict its type. This helps chatbots route to the right handler.\\n\",\"\\n\",\"## Why This Matters\\n\",\"- QA systems need different strategies for factual vs opinion questions.\\n\",\"- Search engines use query classification to choose retrieval methods.\\n\",\"- Customer support bots route differently based on question intent.\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"markdown\",\"metadata\":{},\"source\":[\"## Dataset Overview\\n\",\"Synthetic dataset of 3,000 questions across 6 types.\\n\",\"## Dataset Source: Generated for educational purposes.\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"code\",\"execution_count\":null,\"metadata\":{},\"outputs\":[],\"source\":[\"import subprocess, sys, importlib\\nfor pkg in [\\\"pandas\\\",\\\"numpy\\\",\\\"matplotlib\\\",\\\"seaborn\\\",\\\"scikit-learn\\\"]:\\n    try: importlib.import_module(pkg)\\n    except ImportError: subprocess.check_call([sys.executable,\\\"-m\\\",\\\"pip\\\",\\\"install\\\",\\\"-q\\\",pkg])\\nprint(\\\"Environment ready.\\\")\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"code\",\"execution_count\":null,\"metadata\":{},\"outputs\":[],\"source\":[\"import numpy as np, pandas as pd, matplotlib.pyplot as plt, seaborn as sns\\nimport warnings; warnings.filterwarnings('ignore')\\nsns.set_style('whitegrid')\\n%matplotlib inline\\nfrom sklearn.feature_extraction.text import TfidfVectorizer\\nfrom sklearn.linear_model import LogisticRegression\\nfrom sklearn.ensemble import RandomForestClassifier\\nfrom sklearn.metrics import accuracy_score, classification_report, confusion_matrix, f1_score\\nfrom sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split\\nprint('Imports loaded.')\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"code\",\"execution_count\":null,\"metadata\":{},\"outputs\":[],\"source\":[\"SEED = 42; np.random.seed(SEED); rng = np.random.default_rng(SEED)\\nTYPES = ['Factual','Opinion','Procedural','Causal','Yes/No','Comparison']\\n\\ntemplates = {\\n    'Factual': ['What is the capital of {}?','Who invented {}?','When was {} founded?','Where is {} located?','What year did {} happen?'],\\n    'Opinion': ['What do you think about {}?','Is {} good or bad?','How do you feel about {}?','Should we support {}?','Do you like {}?'],\\n    'Procedural': ['How do I install {}?','What are the steps to {}?','How can I configure {}?','What is the process for {}?','How to set up {}?'],\\n    'Causal': ['Why does {} happen?','What causes {}?','Why is {} important?','What leads to {}?','Why did {} fail?'],\\n    'Yes/No': ['Is {} free?','Does {} support Python?','Can I use {} offline?','Has {} been updated?','Will {} work on Linux?'],\\n    'Comparison': ['What is the difference between {} and {}?','How does {} compare to {}?','{} vs {} which is better?','Should I choose {} or {}?']\\n}\\nfillers = ['Python','JavaScript','Docker','Kubernetes','React','TensorFlow','AWS','MongoDB','Linux','machine learning',\\n           'deep learning','blockchain','climate change','renewable energy','education reform']\\n\\nrows = []\\nfor _ in range(3000):\\n    qtype = rng.choice(TYPES)\\n    tmpl = rng.choice(templates[qtype])\\n    n_blanks = tmpl.count('{}')\\n    fills = rng.choice(fillers, size=n_blanks).tolist()\\n    text = tmpl.format(*fills)\\n    rows.append({'text': text, 'question_type': qtype})\\n\\ndf = pd.DataFrame(rows)\\nprint(f'Shape: {df.shape}'); print(df['question_type'].value_counts()); df.head()\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"markdown\",\"metadata\":{},\"source\":[\"## Data Validation\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"code\",\"execution_count\":null,\"metadata\":{},\"outputs\":[],\"source\":[\"print(f'Missing: {df.isnull().sum().sum()}, Duplicates: {df.duplicated().sum()}')\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"markdown\",\"metadata\":{},\"source\":[\"## EDA\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"code\",\"execution_count\":null,\"metadata\":{},\"outputs\":[],\"source\":[\"fig, axes = plt.subplots(1,2,figsize=(12,4))\\ndf['question_type'].value_counts().plot(kind='bar',ax=axes[0],color='steelblue')\\naxes[0].set_title('Question Type Distribution'); axes[0].tick_params(axis='x',rotation=45)\\ndf['text_len'] = df['text'].str.len()\\ndf.boxplot(column='text_len',by='question_type',ax=axes[1])\\naxes[1].set_title('Text Length by Type'); plt.suptitle('')\\nplt.tight_layout(); plt.show()\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"markdown\",\"metadata\":{},\"source\":[\"## Feature Engineering & Baseline\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"code\",\"execution_count\":null,\"metadata\":{},\"outputs\":[],\"source\":[\"from sklearn.preprocessing import LabelEncoder\\nle = LabelEncoder()\\ndf['label'] = le.fit_transform(df['question_type'])\\n\\nX_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(df['text'], df['label'], test_size=0.2, random_state=SEED, stratify=df['label'])\\n\\ntfidf = TfidfVectorizer(max_features=5000, ngram_range=(1,2))\\nX_tr = tfidf.fit_transform(X_train); X_te = tfidf.transform(X_test)\\n\\nlr = LogisticRegression(max_iter=1000, random_state=SEED)\\nlr.fit(X_tr, y_train)\\ny_pred = lr.predict(X_te)\\n\\nprint('=== Baseline: TF-IDF + LogReg ===')\\nprint(f'Accuracy: {accuracy_score(y_test, y_pred):.4f}')\\nprint(f'Macro F1: {f1_score(y_test, y_pred, average=\\\"macro\\\"):.4f}')\\nprint(classification_report(y_test, y_pred, target_names=le.classes_))\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"markdown\",\"metadata\":{},\"source\":[\"## Evaluation\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"code\",\"execution_count\":null,\"metadata\":{},\"outputs\":[],\"source\":[\"cm = confusion_matrix(y_test, y_pred)\\nplt.figure(figsize=(8,6))\\nsns.heatmap(cm, annot=True, fmt='d', cmap='Blues', xticklabels=le.classes_, yticklabels=le.classes_)\\nplt.title('Confusion Matrix'); plt.xlabel('Predicted'); plt.ylabel('Actual')\\nplt.tight_layout(); plt.show()\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"markdown\",\"metadata\":{},\"source\":[\"## Error Analysis\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"code\",\"execution_count\":null,\"metadata\":{},\"outputs\":[],\"source\":[\"err = pd.DataFrame({'text':X_test.values,'true':y_test.values,'pred':y_pred})\\nwrong = err[err['true']!=err['pred']]\\nprint(f'Errors: {len(wrong)}/{len(err)}')\\nfor _,r in wrong.head(5).iterrows():\\n    print(f'  True={le.classes_[r[\\\"true\\\"]]} Pred={le.classes_[r[\\\"pred\\\"]]}: {r[\\\"text\\\"][:80]}')\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"markdown\",\"metadata\":{},\"source\":[\"## Insights\\n\",\"1. **Question type is largely determined by the opening wh-word** (what/why/how/is/does).\\n\",\"2. **TF-IDF captures these patterns effectively** since question types have distinctive vocabulary.\\n\",\"3. **Comparison questions are hardest** when they use ambiguous phrasing.\\n\",\"\\n\",\"## Limitations\\n\",\"- Synthetic data — real questions are more varied and ambiguous.\\n\",\"- Some questions genuinely span multiple types.\\n\",\"- Doesn't handle non-English questions.\\n\",\"\\n\",\"## How to Improve\\n\",\"1. Use real question datasets (e.g., TREC QC, Yahoo Answers).\\n\",\"2. Add syntactic features (dependency parsing, POS tags).\\n\",\"3. Fine-tune a transformer for nuanced classification.\\n\",\"\\n\",\"## Production Considerations\\n\",\"- Use as a routing layer before QA pipelines.\\n\",\"- Monitor for new question patterns over time.\\n\",\"\\n\",\"## Common Mistakes\\n\",\"1. Overfitting to question templates instead of learning real patterns.\\n\",\"2. Not handling multi-type questions.\\n\",\"\\n\",\"## Mini Challenge\\n\",\"1. Add 2 more question types (definition, hypothetical).\\n\",\"2. Use spaCy POS tags as additional features.\\n\",\"\\n\",\"## Summary\\n\",\"- **Question type classification helps route queries to appropriate handlers.**\\n\",\"- **Simple features (wh-words, TF-IDF) work well for structured question types.**\\n\",\"- **Real-world deployment needs diverse training data and continuous updates.**\"]}\n",
    " ],\n",
